text: Seveux-Motey is a commune in the Haute-Saône department in the region of Bourgogne-Franche-Comté in eastern France. It was established on 1 January 2019 by merger of the former communes of Seveux (the seat) and Motey-sur- Saône.Arrêté préfectoral 19 December 2018 ==See also== *Communes of the Haute-Saône department ==References== Category:Communes of Haute-Saône Category:Populated places established in 2019
title: Seveux-Motey
